commitResults.messageTitle: Add save and load from data feature
commitResults.messageBody:
After users adds tasks to their task list, the data is stored into userdata.txt
* After every command that the user uses, the data is written in the userdata.txt to ensure that all the changes are properly saved.
* If userdata.txt does not exist, it will be created.

On initial launch of the chatbot, data from the userdata.txt is loaded if applicable
* If userdata.txt does not exist, no entries will be loaded
* If there are corrupted entries, it will not be loaded and the user will be informed
* User will get information on how many entries were successfully loaded

commitResults.messageTitle: Add datetime for deadline and event tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
Deadline tasks now require the /by field to be a date and could optionally include a time.

Event tasks now require the /from field and /to field to be a date and could optionally include a time.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add classes for Parser, Storage and TaskList
commitResults.messageBody:
Created a new Storage class which handles
* Reading of data from userdata.txt
* Writing to userdata.txt

Created a new Parser class which handles
* Creating new Tasks (ToDos, Deadlines, EventTask)

Created a new TaskList class which handles
* adding of Task
* removing of Task at index
* marking Task as completed at index
* unmarking Task as incomplete at index
* exporting all the tasks

UI class
* Takes care of all the UI elements of the chatbot (printing)
* Reads input from the user

Parser class
* Now parses the user command and returns a command class which can be executed later

Command classes
* Every command has its own respective command class now. Calling execute() will run the respective code for each command.
Reorganize the classes into packages
